L’UNIONE SAMMARINESE OPERATORI DEL TURISMO (USOT), è l’organizzazione professionale legalmente riconosciuta degli operatori economici del settore della ricezione, della ristorazione e dell’iniziativa turistica.

Dal 1963, tutela gli interessi e i diritti degli operatori della filiera turistica – commerciale ed offre servizi di consulenza del lavoro, assistenza legislativa, amministrativa, fiscale e sindacale. 

Inoltre ogni anno propone ai propri associati corsi di formazione gratuiti e promuove il territorio sammarinese e i propri associati sui canali web.
Gli scopi principali dell’Associazione sono quelli di:

promuovere lo sviluppo e l’affermazione materiale e morale della categoria quale fattore insostituibile di progresso e di incremento economico;
promuovere la posizione, lo studio e la soluzione dei problemi interessanti la categoria in vista della sua natura tipicamente imprenditoriale e delle particolari esigenze tecniche ed economiche che ne caratterizzano l’attività;
coordinare l’attività dei consociati in ordine al progresso tecnologico, economico, morale e organizzativo del Settore mediante la disciplina dei rapporti di concorrenza e colleganza, delle condizioni di mercato;
tutelare i diritti dei consociati non contrastanti con l’interesse generale della categoria predisponendo a tal fine, l’assistenza e la consulenza legale e commerciale;
collaborare con gli organi pubblici predisposti per la formulazione e la soluzione dei problemi generali e di settore delle attività turistiche;
di fare quindi tutti ciò che nell’interesse della categoria concorra, nell’ambito delle leggi e dei regolamenti, alla superiore finalità di potenziamento turistico della Repubblica di San Marino.

Founded in 1902 as the WV Society of Osteopathic Medicine, the West Virginia Osteopathic Medical Association has served West Virginia for over 120 years. Our executive office is located in Lewisburg, WV.

The Association strives to:

Encourage the understanding of osteopathic medicine;
Elevate and maintain high standards of osteopathic institutions;
Advance professional knowledge of surgery, obstetrics, and the diagnosis, prevention and treatment of disease in general;
Stimulate research and disseminate results;
Maintain ethical conduct in all phases of osteopathic medicine and surgery.


The mission of the West Virginia Osteopathic Medical Association is to promote public health:

By the elevation and maintenance of high standards of osteopathic education;
By the stimulation of research and investigation;
By the collection and dissemination of such knowledge for the education and improvement of the profession and for the benefit of humanity.

An association of Professional body for individuals from both the Publics & Private Sectors who have been certified (i.e. as Certified Integrity Officers, CeiO) by the Corporate Integrity Development Centre (CIDC), Malaysia Anti-Corruption Academy (MACA) of the Malaysian Anti-Corruption Commission (a.k.a. Suruhanjaya Pecegahan Anti Rasuah, SPRM). Hence, the Association of Certified Integrity Officers (ACeiO).

ACeiO was registered as a professional body ("Badan Ikhtisas") via the Registrar of Societies Malaysia (ROS) on 21.10.2013 ("PERSATUAN PEGAWAI INTEGRITI BERTAULIAH MALAYSIA") with registration number PPM-018-14-21102013.

Its Objectives are as follows:
1. To become a driving force behind the national integrity agenda, as well as anti-corruption and ethical values in collaboration with public agencies, government-interested companies such as Government Linked Companies (GLCs), Government Link Investment Companies (GLICs), Government Owned Companies (GOCs), statutory & private bodies, along with appropriate regional & international cooperation;

2. Foster a culture of Integrity through the implementation of the national integrity plan and the current national anti-corruption plan/strategy;

3. Implement an Integrity culture program via education, prevention, & other appropriate approach;

4. Produce relevant literature, articles, or relevant sharing sessions;

5. Bring together similar skilled and passionate individuals; and

6. Bringing together the CeiOs via this ACeiO as a platform to share ideas, views, suggestions, & challenges in playing the role of CeiO in their respective agencies or employers, as well as inviting them to join as members of ACeiO to uphold the torch of integrity, ethics, & anti-corruption values.

ACeiO was established via a Direction issued by The Right Hon. Prime Minster in 2009 (i.e., Arahan YAB Perdana Menteri No.1 Tahun 2009, Siri 1 No.1 Tahun 2011) Pelaksanaan Program Pegawai Integriti Bertauliah.

