L'association a pour objectif :
- de valoriser, de faire connaître et reconnaître vis-à-vis des tiers (sociétés privées, associations, État, organismes institutionnels, collectivités territoriales, structure publiques et parapubliques, syndicats…) le groupe des anciens élèves de l’EPMN, ci-après nommés anciens élèves ;
- d’animer et de développer le réseau des anciens élèves, tant en France qu’à l’étranger, de créer et de maintenir entre eux des liens professionnels, d’entraide et amicaux ;  
- de contribuer au développement et à la qualité de la formation initiale des élèves ainsi qu’au maintien de la qualité des diplômes délivrés par l’EPMN à ses étudiants ;  
- d’apporter aide et conseil aux membres de l’Association dans le développement de leurs activités professionnelles ; 
- de développer la promotion, la diffusion et l’exploitation des savoirs et des expériences en valorisant les compétences individuelles par l’organisation de colloques, conférences, journées d’études, formations, webinairs, débats et par l’édition, la diffusion de documentations scientifiques et techniques ;  
- de renforcer et développer les liens avec les structures des anciens élèves (entreprises privées, associations, collectivités territoriales, structures parapubliques, services de l’État…) ainsi qu’avec les structures institutionnelles représentatives du milieu professionnel dans lequel évoluent les anciens élèves ;  
- et, plus généralement, de contribuer au développement d’activités ou d’organiser toutes actions susceptibles de concourir à l'objet social de l'Association.

Infermieri Bari è una rete professionale composta da infermieri liberi professionisti operanti su tutto il territorio della provincia di Bari.

Il progetto nasce con l’obiettivo di:
	•	Valorizzare la libera professione infermieristica;
	•	Coordinare in modo etico e trasparente l’assistenza infermieristica domiciliare;
	•	Promuovere una cultura professionale condivisa;
	•	Contrastare il lavoro sommerso;
	•	Facilitare il collegamento tra cittadini e infermieri territoriali.

Ogni iscritto opera nel rispetto di un regolamento comune, con tariffe allineate, presa in carico geolocalizzata e fatturazione regolare.

La rete è organizzata in un gruppo attivo, un sito web dedicato, un numero unico per i pazienti e un Direttivo eletto democraticamente.

 Se sei un infermiere libero professionista a Bari e provincia, unisciti al progetto.
 Se sei un cittadino, puoi contare su una rete seria, affidabile e professionale.

Justice administrative collective et indépendante (JACI) est un syndicat fondé le 17 janvier 2025 représentant tout·e juge administratif·ve, en activité ou non.

JACI défend et milite pour un service public de la justiceadministrative de qualité, qui soit avant tout au service des justiciables.

Pour ce faire, le syndicat :

1. Veille à ce que les conditions effectives du procès équitable et le respect des droits humains et des libertés fondamentales, seuls à même de garantir le maintien de l’Etat de droit, soient assurés à tous·tes, de façon égale ;

2. Promeut le modèle d’une magistrature de carrière, afin de protéger l’indépendance et l’impartialité des juges administratif·ves ainsi que le rétablissement desconditions de travail protectrices de l’autonomie des magistrat·es ;

3. Se tourne vers l’extérieur pour promouvoir un service public ouvert sur les justiciables, en s’associant étroitement à l’ensemble des acteurs·rices du service public de la justice et en participant à une réflexion critique sur la façon dont le droit est produit et sur les conséquences des textes envisagés ou adoptés.

A APTAD - Associação Portuguesa de Transportadores em Automóveis Descaracterizados é a voz das empresas operadoras TVDE em Portugal.

Representamos o setor junto das autoridades públicas, das plataformas eletrónicas e da sociedade, defendendo as condições necessárias para uma atividade sustentável, justa e transparente.

A APTAD trabalha para garantir:
 - Regras claras e equilibradas entre operadores, motoristas e plataformas;
 - Tarifas e comissões justas que assegurem a viabilidade das empresas;
 - Formação e fiscalização rigorosa para um serviço seguro e profissional;
 - Dados e políticas públicas baseadas em factos e transparência;
 - Uma transição ecológica real, com incentivos à mobilidade elétrica.

Como representante institucional dos operadores licenciados, a APTAD participa ativamente no processo legislativo, propõe soluções técnicas e colabora com entidades como a AMT, o IMT, o Governo e o Parlamento, sempre com o objetivo de valorizar as empresas TVDE e o trabalho dos seus profissionais.

Missão: Representar e defender as empresas operadoras TVDE.
Visão: Um setor moderno, sustentável e respeitado no ecossistema da mobilidade em Portugal.

The Women’s Bar Association of Maryland (“WBA”) is an organization of women and men committed to the full and equal participation of women in the legal profession and in a just society. The WBA believes that a strong community of women in the legal profession is essential to the administration of justice.

The mission and goals of the WBA are to:

* Promote and assist women to obtain positions of influence and leadership within their workplace, the legal profession, the judiciary, and the community;

* Raise awareness of and fight biases against women within the community at large, the legal profession, and under the law;

* Promote and effect diversity, equality, and justice under the law and within the legal system;

* Support women in the legal profession in their personal and professional lives;

* Provide opportunities for volunteerism and advocacy on issues affecting women;

* Collaborate with other individuals and organizations to improve the status of women;

* Celebrate the individual and collective achievements of women in the legal profession; and

* Promote full and equal participation of women in society by eliminating all forms of discrimination.

The Women's Bar Association of Maryland (WBA) is a specialty bar association of women and men supporting women in the legal profession and working for equal rights and opportunities for women in the legal profession and the community.  The WBA offers its members opportunities for personal and professional growth, networking and business development, and leadership through its: Programs, Committees, Local County Chapters, Online forums, and  Website and online resources.

The WBA’s diverse membership is comprised of female and male lawyers, judges, government and elected officials, and law school students. Our members represent all areas of the state, and form 11 local chapters.

New York Chiropractic Council is a professional organization that promotes the philosophy, science and art of chiropractic. To protect the welfare of its members to practice chiropractic without compromise, and with parity and respect; To protect the public`s ability to receive chiropractic without prejudice, ridicule or financial penalty from any individual, group or profession  
To conduct educational seminars, lectures and meetings within the profession and the public in accordance with our stated objectives;

To Stand Out To keep chiropractic separate and distinct from all other professions; To Respect To foster inter-professional relations based upon mutual respect and a clear understanding of the basic Philosophy, Science and Art of Chiropractic.

The VGFOA engages in a broad array of activities that include: 

Providing education opportunities to members through the VGFOA certification program, as well as other training courses that best meet membership training needs; 
Providing networking and education opportunities to members and vendors at Fall and Spring conferences; 
Serving as the liaison to VGFOA's regional organizations (Northern Virginia, Central Virginia, Hampton Roads Area, and Southwest Virginia) in providing for the educational needs within the organization; 
Updating members on the impact of actions taken by standard-setting bodies (GASB, OMB, etc.) with a suggested educational program designed to orient members to proposed changes in standards; 
Providing to members a State legislative update in a timely manner and working with officials on legislative issues that affect VGFOA members; 
Providing scholarship and award opportunities to members; 
Providing oversight of the solicitation and production of virtually all content delivered to the membership via newsletter, website, and/or e-mail distribution outlets, and managing related technologies (e.g., e-mail distribution) in order for content providers to best communicate to the membership and other interested parties; and 
Providing oversight of any advertising for sponsor programs, scholarships, training programs, and newsletters, including exhibitors for Fall and Spring conferences and vendor relations to promote services via the website and/or newsletter.

Nous sommes une Structure de développement économique local. APESI BURKINA (Action pour la Promotion de l’Entrepreneuriat et des Systèmes d’Irrigation) est une nouvelle démarche qui incarne et regroupe des professionnels des questions de résiliences, des changements climatiques, des innovations technologiques, d’agri business, de l’entrepreneuriat social et responsable, de l’équité et du genre. Ces derniers ont décidé dans une synergie d’action de mettre en évidence leurs expériences et leurs compétences au service du développement durable.

NOS ACTIONS visent à :
• Susciter l’entrepreneuriat et de promouvoir la formation professionnelle des  jeunes et
des  femmes en vue de leur insertion socio-économique ;
• Promouvoir l’économie verte; 
• Proposer des solutions technologiques innovantes pour un meilleur accès à  l’eau potable
et aux ouvrages d’assainissement;
